  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "Linking your Aadhaar card to your State Bank of India (SBI) account is a relatively straightforward process and can typically be done through several methods: online, SMS, ATM, or by visiting an SBI branch. Below are the steps for each method:\n\n### 1. **Online Method via SBI Internet Banking:**\n\n1. **Log in** to your SBI internet banking account.\n2. **Navigate to the 'My Accounts' section** and select 'Link Your Aadhaar Number'.\n3. **Select your Account Number** and enter your Aadhaar number.\n4. **Submit** the details.\n5. **Confirmation**: You will receive a confirmation message on your screen and via SMS once your Aadhaar is successfully linked.\n\n### 2. **Through SMS:**\n\n1. **Compose a new SMS** in the following format: UID(space)Aadhaar Number(space)Account Number.\n2. **Send the SMS** to 567676.\n3. **Confirmation**: You will receive a confirmation message via SMS once your Aadhaar is successfully linked.\n\n### 3. **Using SBI ATM:**\n\n1. **Visit any SBI ATM**.\n2. **Insert your ATM card** and enter your PIN.\n3. **Select the 'Service' option**.\n4. **Choose 'Aadhaar Registration'**.\n5. **Select 'Account Type'** (Savings/Current).\n6. **Enter your Aadhaar Number** and confirm.\n7. **Confirmation**: You will receive a confirmation message on your screen and via SMS once your Aadhaar is successfully linked.\n\n### 4. **Visiting an SBI Branch:**\n\n1. **Visit your nearest SBI branch**.\n2. **Carry a photocopy and original Aadhaar card** and your bank passbook.\n3. **Fill out the Aadhaar Linking Form** provided by the bank.\n4. **Submit the form** along with the photocopy of your Aadhaar card.\n5. **Confirmation**: The bank will verify and process your request. You will receive a confirmation once your Aadhaar is successfully linked.\n\n### 5. **Through SBI Mobile App:**\n\n1. **Log in** to the SBI mobile app.\n2. **Navigate to 'Service Requests'** or 'Requests' section.\n3. **Select 'Link Aadhaar'**.\n4. **Enter your Aadhaar number** and submit.\n5. **Confirmation**: You will receive a confirmation message on your screen and via SMS once your Aadhaar is successfully linked.\n\n### **Important Notes:**\n\n- Ensure that your mobile number is registered with your Aadhaar and SBI account for seamless communication.\n- Always verify the details to avoid any errors during the linking process.\n\nIf you encounter any issues or need further assistance, kindly contact SBI customer service or visit the nearest branch for support.",
